# Portfolio `/past` project pages

## Required sections (in order)

Every **project deep-dive** (`app/past/<slug>/page.tsx`) must include:

1. **Header** ‚Äî Eyebrow badge, title, primary actions: **View source** (GitHub), **Live** (external), **View Gallery** (`<Link href="/gallery">` with orange `ImageIcon`, matching Altar / other pages).

2. **The Discovery** ‚Äî Section heading with `Search` icon; lead copy explaining the problem space / insight.

3. **The Purpose** ‚Äî Sidebar-style card (right column on md+) with `Sparkles` icon and short italic purpose statement.

4. **Quote** ‚Äî Pull-quote block with `MessageSquareQuote` inside the Discovery column (same pattern as Altar).

5. **The Friction** ‚Äî Card with `ShieldAlert`; what was wrong with status quo.

6. **The Solve** ‚Äî Card with `Zap`; what you built / how it addresses friction.

7. **Technical Snapshot** ‚Äî `Terminal` icon + heading; grid of label/value pairs (stack, deploy, core loop, etc.).

8. **Footer** ‚Äî ‚ÄúEnd of Transmission‚Äù strip (optional but consistent on completed pages).

Match spacing and Tailwind patterns from `app/past/altar/page.tsx` unless there is a deliberate redesign.

## `/past` hub (`app/past/page.tsx`) accent colors

Assign **one Tailwind hue per project** for folder icon + hover arrow. **Do not reuse** an existing project‚Äôs hue.

Current reservation:

| Project      | Hue     | Classes (example)                    |
|-------------|---------|--------------------------------------|
| Orbit       | emerald | `bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400` |
| Altar       | violet  | `bg-violet-500/10 text-violet-400`   |
| Mustafa.ai  | cyan    | `bg-cyan-500/10 text-cyan-400`        |
| QuickBooks  | blue    | `bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-400`       |

For a **new** project, pick an unused hue (e.g. **rose**, **orange**, **fuchsia**, **amber**) and add a row to this rule.

## Home Past pillar order (Archive)

The three cards follow **recency**, not a permanent ‚Äúflagship.‚Äù **Newest completed project first.**

The small status label on each card (bottom right) should read **`Completed`** for every project in this pillar‚Äîincluding shipped apps that still have a live URL‚Äîso the Archive reads consistently.

- **With Supabase:** `app/page.tsx` loads up to **80** completed projects (not 3), then **`mergePastPillarProjects`** merges in **`STATIC_ARCHIVE_FILL`** rows only for **missing slugs** (`orbit`, `altar`, `mustafa-ai`). Everything is sorted by `created_at` desc and **sliced to 3**. DB rows win when the slug exists (your CMS dates matter).
- **Empty DB:** Same merge with zero rows ‚Üí static fill only.
- **Optional DB sync:** To store Orbit/Altar in Supabase for CMS parity, use `supabase/snippets/seed_projects_archive.sql` as a template in the SQL Editor (adjust columns to your schema).
